Adult male.description: Adult male Brown-headed Cowbirds are smaller with a shorter bill and a smaller head than male Bronzed Cowbirds Male which have a heavy bill and thick neck. Also note eye color difference; dark on Brown-headed and red on Bronzed.

Female.description: Female Brown-headed Cowbirds are smaller with a shorter and less heavy bill compared to female Bronzed Cowbirds, which have a hefty bill. Also note eye color difference; dark on Brown-headed and red on Bronzed.

Male.description: Male Shiny Cowbirds have a thinner bill and lacks red eyes and neck ruff of male Bronzed Cowbirds.

Female.description: Female Shiny Cowbirds are paler overall than female Bronzed Cowbirds with a dark eye (female Bronzed Cowbirds have a red eye).

Adult male.description: Brewer's Blackbirds have a thinner bill than Bronzed Cowbirds, which have a thick and hefty bill. Adult male Brewer's Blackbirds have yellow eyes while Bronzed Cowbirds have red eyes.

Female.description: Brewer's Blackbirds have a thinner bill than Bronzed Cowbirds, which have a thick and hefty bill. Females are generally darker overall than female Bronzed Cowbirds.

Adult male.description: Overall Common Grackles appear slimmer and more elongated compared to the compact Bronzed Cowbird. They also have a yellow eye whereas Bronzed Cowbirds have a red eye.
